Class Lass,<br><br>
Thanks for the post. What sticks out the most is the part about forgiveness.<br><br>
If I had been taken out in a basket, with five bullet holes, forgiving probably would be a commodity I couldn't afford. there are many who paid a greater price and bore a greater burden than I.<br><br>
You are right, and we all know it. &quot;...forgive us our sins *AS* we forgive those who trespass against us...&quot; I stumble everyday. I pick myself up and start once again. <br><br>
Life is not easy, but it is betterfor me because I am able to look past alot of the wrongs and the broken promises that went along with being a soldier who served in Vietnam. I am fortunate to have this ability. Not everyone is like me. So, as Ed suggests, I am only able to speak for me.<br><br>
Getting back to your thoughts on forgiveness: whatever it is that leads us to forgive those who have wronged us does us - the *forgivers* - far more good than the person we are forgiving. I firmly believe that.<br><br>
Thanks for your post and for the b/c.<br><br>
Peace to you and the kids.
